## How API Clients Authenticate

```http
POST /connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials
&client_id=<ClientGuid>
&client_secret=<rawSecret>
&scope=magiq-api
```

Response:
```json
{
  "access_token": "eyJ...",
  "expires_in": 3600,
  "token_type": "Bearer",
  "scope": "magiq-api"
}
```

The access token is a signed JWT. The `TenantId` claim is present (baked in via `Client.Claims`). Consuming APIs validate it via the existing `JwtBearer` middleware and read `TenantId` identically to user tokens.

The `aud` claim will be `https://{domain}/resources` (IS4 static audience via `EmitStaticAudienceClaim = true`). Consuming APIs that need scope enforcement check the `scope` claim.

---

